						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into the wall of Rāmaliṅga temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Tribhuvanamalla (Vikramāditya VI)—A.D. 1098.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Bahudhānya, Āśvayuja, puṇṇame, Monday,</hi> falling in the reign of Tribhuvanamalla and regularly corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1098, September 13.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription is badly damaged and effaced. It seems to register a gift to god Svayaṁbhū-Rāmēs11vara, and others. It refers to the trade-guild of the 500 <hi rend="italic">svāmis</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Ayyāvoḷe.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
